/** Define a simple date format object.  
NOTE: Set the locale of the date format to English since the XSD:dateTime 
format is used which is locale agnostic.*/

public class Test {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        final long lNow = System.currentTimeMillis();

        Locale.setDefault(new Locale("ar","EG"));
        
        ExtendedDataElement element = 
EventFactory.eINSTANCE.createExtendedDataElement();

        element.setValuesAsDateAsLong(lNow);
        
        long value = element.getValuesAsDateAsLong();
        
        System.out.println(lNow == value);      
    }
}

public class Test {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
       
        Locale.setDefault(new Locale("ar","SA"));        
            
        CommonBaseEvent commonBaseEvent = 
EventFactory.eINSTANCE.createCommonBaseEvent();
        commonBaseEvent.setCreationTimeAsLong(System.currentTimeMillis());
        
        System.out.println("LONG: " + commonBaseEvent.getCreationTimeAsLong());
        System.out.println("LOCALE: "+Locale.getDefault());
    }
}

Bug.WithStack:
Please consider the following scenario:
1      long lNow = System.currentTimeMillis();
2      element.setValuesAsDateAsLong(lNow);
3      long value = element.getValuesAsDateAsLong();
4      assertEquals(lNow, value);

This test fails at line 3 due to this exception :

 java.lang.IllegalStateException: 2004-07-01T09:27:48.773Z is not a valid 
xsd:dateTime
 at 
org.eclipse.hyades.logging.events.cbe.impl.ExtendedDataElementImpl.getValuesAsDa
teAsLong(Line:3)

Also When I use the following code:
1      long lNow = System.currentTimeMillis();
2      element.setValuesAsDateAsLong(lNow);
3      String StringValue = (String)element.getValues().get(0);
4      long value = Date.parse(StringValue);
5      assertEquals(lNow, value);

This test fails at line 4 due to this exception :

 java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
 at java.util.Date.parse(Date.java:593)
 at Line 4.

 So:
 extended element can set date value but fails to get it.
Date value listed in values List are represented as String that is unparsable 
by java.util.Date.parse(String) 
How can we parse that value???

Please Advise

